<div id="review_2358836054" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2358836054" />
    <a title="John" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21938800-john"><img alt="John" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620927870p2/21938800.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2358836054?book_show_action=true">Apr 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John" href="/user/show/21938800-john">John</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099532040" href="/book/show/9286056-the-man-from-beijing">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21938800-john?shelf=scandinavian-crime">scandinavian-crime</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21938800-john?shelf=mankell">mankell</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2358836054" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3912487000805685312">The story starts well with 19 people murdered in an isolated Swedish hamlet. A judge is related to one of the victims and begins to investigate and then the story becomes weird. The story of three Chinese brothers journey to the US in the 1860s and their exploitation. Who did the murders is fairly obvious and the judge is not the sharpest card in the deck. Coupled with a troubled marriage and an illness she looks into the murders but fails to see the nose on her face. <br/><br/>Then there is s polemic abo</span>
  <span id="freeText3912487000805685312" style="display:none">The story starts well with 19 people murdered in an isolated Swedish hamlet. A judge is related to one of the victims and begins to investigate and then the story becomes weird. The story of three Chinese brothers journey to the US in the 1860s and their exploitation. Who did the murders is fairly obvious and the judge is not the sharpest card in the deck. Coupled with a troubled marriage and an illness she looks into the murders but fails to see the nose on her face. <br /><br />Then there is s polemic about China which is bizarre and written by someone who knows very little about China. A frustrating book and surprising when I enjoy the Wallander novels which are so well written. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3912487000805685312" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


